  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You develop a greater sense of your skillset, expanding further into new options to spread your fame further. You can select one of the following benefits:</p><p><strong>Second Exploit</strong>: You gain the Exploit benefit of a different Operative Specialization, but no other benefits. If you select Striker, you apply proficiency increaes with weapons to one-handed melee weapons and unarmed attacks with the agile or finesse traits, instead of replacing your proficiency with firearms. Your Aim also benefits Strikes with these weapons, but these weapons cannot qualify as firearms for Strikes as requirements for Operative feats. If you are a Striker, you apply proficiency increases with weapons to one-handed ranged martial weapons if you select Skirmisher, and to martial weapons in the sniper group if you select Sniper.</p><p><strong>Operative’s Additional Training</strong>: You gain another benefit from your Operative’s Training feature. At 16th level, you can also select an additional benefit.</p>"
